Project 02 · SQL · Risk Scoring · Compliance Automation
Policy Risk Scoring Model — SQL
Composite risk scoring model built from real BSC register data — turning manual governance review into an automated, prioritised, data-driven compliance engine.
SQLCASE WHENDATEDIFFLEFT JOINRisk LogicGovernance
02
📋 Business Problem Solved
121 policies reviewed manually — based on institutional memory. No scoring system. No automation. No audit trail to prove decisions were data-driven. I designed a SQL risk model calculating a composite score per policy using days overdue, missing EIA assessments, no-date flags, and duplicate markers — making governance decisions evidence-based and defensible.
bsc_policy_risk_model.sql — Barnet & Southgate College · Prem Victor 
-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- BSC Policy Compliance Risk Scoring Model
-- Author    : Prem Victor | Business Analyst (Placement)
-- Placement : Barnet & Southgate College, Jun 2025 – Jan 2026
-- Source    : BSC_Policy_Register.xlsx (121 policies, 17 areas)
-- Purpose   : Automated risk prioritisation for executive reporting
-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

SELECT
    p.area,
    p.policy_title,
    p.responsible_manager,
    p.date_of_last_update,
    p.date_of_next_update,
    e.eia_completed,
    p.action_required,
    p.approval_level,

    -- Days overdue calculation
    DATEDIFF(CURDATE(), p.date_of_next_update)  AS days_overdue,

    -- ── COMPOSITE RISK SCORE ─────────────────────────────
    GREATEST(DATEDIFF(CURDATE(), p.date_of_next_update), 0)

    -- EIA not completed: major compliance penalty
    + CASE WHEN e.eia_completed NOT IN ('Yes', 'Completed')
           THEN 50 ELSE 0 END

    -- Duplicate / flagged for removal: governance integrity risk
    + CASE WHEN p.action_required LIKE '%REMOVE%'
           OR p.action_required  LIKE '%Duplicate%'
           THEN 30 ELSE 0 END

    -- No next review date: unmonitorable = high risk
    + CASE WHEN p.date_of_next_update IS NULL
           OR p.date_of_next_update IN ('No date', '??', 'N/A')
           THEN 40 ELSE 0 END

    AS risk_score,

    -- ── RISK CLASSIFICATION ───────────────────────────────
    CASE
      WHEN DATEDIFF(CURDATE(), p.date_of_next_update) > 365
           AND e.eia_completed NOT IN ('Yes') THEN 'CRITICAL'
      WHEN DATEDIFF(CURDATE(), p.date_of_next_update) > 180 THEN 'HIGH'
      WHEN DATEDIFF(CURDATE(), p.date_of_next_update) > 0   THEN 'MEDIUM'
      WHEN p.action_required = 'None required'               THEN 'COMPLIANT'
      ELSE 'MONITOR'
    END                                                     AS risk_level

FROM       bsc_policy_register        p
LEFT JOIN  equality_impact_assessments e ON p.policy_id = e.policy_id
WHERE
    p.date_of_next_update < CURDATE()
    OR p.date_of_next_update IS NULL
    OR p.date_of_next_update IN ('??', 'No date')
ORDER BY
    risk_score   DESC,
    days_overdue DESC
LIMIT 12;
